That's for sure.

255
00:14:27,101 --> 00:14:28,181
Is that thing waterproof?

256
00:14:33,501 --> 00:14:35,181
[chuckles] What do you think?

257
00:14:35,301 --> 00:14:37,861
- I hope so.
- [Trish laughs]

258
00:14:37,941 --> 00:14:39,421
Thank you.

259
00:14:39,821 --> 00:14:41,621
- [sighs]
- [Maddie] Trish, not that

260
00:14:41,701 --> 00:14:43,381
I'm not grateful
that you brought me here,

261
00:14:43,461 --> 00:14:45,221
because I'm really,
really grateful. [Laughs]

262
00:14:46,301 --> 00:14:48,501
But why are you spending
your hard-earned money on this?

263
00:14:49,541 --> 00:14:50,541
Why not?

264
00:14:51,141 --> 00:14:52,141
Hmm?

265
00:14:53,461 --> 00:14:54,781
Thanks.

266
00:14:55,421 --> 00:14:57,901
- ["We Stay Up" playing]
- To the perfect escape?

267
00:14:57,941 --> 00:15:01,501
- [laughs] To the perfect escape.
- [Trish chuckles] Yeah.

268
00:15:01,621 --> 00:15:05,501
[Maddie] I'm going to do it!

269
00:15:17,461 --> 00:15:19,301
- [woman] Hello!
- [girls laughing]

270
00:15:19,421 --> 00:15:21,541
- [woman] Oh, hello.
- You scared us.

271
00:15:21,621 --> 00:15:24,101
What about a flower
may help you feel better?

272
00:15:24,221 --> 00:15:26,141
- Oh, that's so sweet.
- It's so beautiful for you.

273
00:15:26,261 --> 00:15:26,941
- Thanks.
- [woman] It's good for you.

274
00:15:27,061 --> 00:15:28,741
Here you go.

275
00:15:28,861 --> 00:15:31,061
Oh, thank you. Oh, too much.
Here, you take it.

276
00:15:31,181 --> 00:15:32,541
No, no, no, no, no. Keep it.

277
00:15:32,621 --> 00:15:34,421
- Very kind.
- [Trish] But...

278
00:15:34,501 --> 00:15:35,501
- do you think we could have...
- [woman] Very kind.

279
00:15:35,581 --> 00:15:36,901
The whales instead?

280
00:15:36,941 --> 00:15:37,941
- [woman] Of course.
- Mummy whale

281
00:15:38,061 --> 00:15:39,581
and, uh, baby whale.

282
00:15:39,701 --> 00:15:40,821
- Yes, you can.
- Thank you so much.

283
00:15:40,941 --> 00:15:41,941
Why?

284
00:15:43,181 --> 00:15:44,221
Maybe it's a clue.

285
00:15:45,661 --> 00:15:46,821
- A clue?
- [Trish] Mm-hmm.

286
00:15:46,901 --> 00:15:47,901
[chuckles] To what?

287
00:15:48,461 --> 00:15:50,941
The subject of your final piece.

288
00:15:51,021 --> 00:15:53,461
- Yes.
- You and, uh, Chad's

289
00:15:54,021 --> 00:15:55,061
favorite whale.

290
00:15:55,141 --> 00:15:56,181
What was her name?

291
00:15:56,821 --> 00:15:57,901
Ceto.

292
00:15:57,941 --> 00:15:58,941
Maybe...

293
00:16:00,221 --> 00:16:01,821
we came all the way here so that

294
00:16:01,901 --> 00:16:04,261
you could, uh, meet an old friend.

295
00:16:05,061 --> 00:16:06,261
Trish.

296
00:16:06,941 --> 00:16:08,541
What?

297
00:16:08,621 --> 00:16:10,341
It's all you and Chad ever talked about.

298
00:16:10,421 --> 00:16:11,101
- You're joking.
- What do you mean? What's wrong?

299
00:16:11,221 --> 00:16:12,261
Maddie.

300
00:16:12,461 --> 00:16:14,461
[somber music playing]

301
00:16:15,461 --> 00:16:17,941
Um, you can have the mummy whale.

302
00:16:18,101 --> 00:16:19,341
- [woman] Thank you.
- I'm going to deal

303
00:16:19,421 --> 00:16:20,901
with my grumpy friend. Hey!

304
00:16:27,061 --> 00:16:28,101
[exhales heavily]

305
00:16:28,181 --> 00:16:30,661
[somber music continues]

306
00:16:34,661 --> 00:16:35,661
[Trish] Hey!

307
00:16:37,021 --> 00:16:38,301
I thought you would love this.

308
00:16:39,061 --> 00:16:40,301
No, Trish.

309
00:16:41,581 --> 00:16:43,581
- Why?
- [Maddie] Trish, I love you,

310
00:16:43,661 --> 00:16:45,941
but I'm not paying to endorse
to see Ceto in captivity.

311
00:16:46,101 --> 00:16:49,741
And her baby died two years ago
in that awful tank of pneumonia

312
00:16:49,821 --> 00:16:51,581
or so they said. It was obviously a lot.

313
00:16:51,661 --> 00:16:54,221
But we came... [chuckles]
all the way out here

314
00:16:54,301 --> 00:16:55,341
from the other side of the world,

315
00:16:55,421 --> 00:16:57,461
to see Ceto in person.

316
00:16:57,541 --> 00:16:59,221
Like you and Chad, never could before.

317
00:16:59,301 --> 00:17:00,781
Yes, because they were in the wild.

318
00:17:01,261 --> 00:17:02,501
Which is where they're meant to be,

319
00:17:02,621 --> 00:17:03,781
not confined to a fish tank.

320
00:17:05,861 --> 00:17:07,501
Okay. You know what? I...

321
00:17:08,861 --> 00:17:11,101
I totally misread the situation.
You're... you're right.

322
00:17:11,941 --> 00:17:13,381
We... we can do something else.

323
00:17:14,061 --> 00:17:15,501
Anything else. Okay just.

324
00:17:18,261 --> 00:17:19,941
Just enjoy our holiday.

325
00:17:20,101 --> 00:17:21,101
Can we please...

326
00:17:21,581 --> 00:17:23,341
- [soft music playing]
- Okay.

327
00:17:24,261 --> 00:17:25,781
Okay, fine.

328
00:17:25,861 --> 00:17:26,781
- What do you want to do?
- [Trish] Yes!

329
00:17:26,861 --> 00:17:28,061
Uh, two things to do.

330
00:17:28,181 --> 00:17:29,701
We start with the alcohol.

331
00:17:29,781 --> 00:17:31,341
And then, we'll see where we land.

332
00:17:33,181 --> 00:17:35,381
[Trish] So, paddle-boarding lessons?

333
00:17:35,461 --> 00:17:37,221
- What do you think? Yeah.
- [Josh] Paddle boarding lessons?

334
00:17:37,301 --> 00:17:39,101
[Josh] It's easy,
you know, you'll figure it out.

335
00:17:39,181 --> 00:17:40,621
- [Trish] Yeah, but you know...
- [Maddie] Here you go.

336
00:17:40,741 --> 00:17:41,861
[Trish] Maddie!

337
00:17:42,381 --> 00:17:44,261
- Hey.
- [Trish] This is Josh.

338
00:17:44,341 --> 00:17:46,541
I'm trying to get him to give us
some paddle boarding lessons

339
00:17:46,661 --> 00:17:49,301
'cause staying upright
is not really my forte, so...

340
00:17:50,021 --> 00:17:50,941
[Maddie clears throat]

341
00:17:51,101 --> 00:17:52,101
[Josh laughs]

342
00:17:52,861 --> 00:17:54,421
Hey, uh, that place is a dump.

343
00:17:55,181 --> 00:17:56,861
And I prefer to see them out there.

344
00:17:58,181 --> 00:17:59,821
- Where they belong.
- Exactly.

345
00:18:00,861 --> 00:18:02,101
Out in the wild.

346
00:18:03,141 --> 00:18:05,261
Where they're meant to be,
not confined to some fish tank.

347
00:18:05,381 --> 00:18:07,221
Exactly. And that whale there?

348
00:18:07,341 --> 00:18:09,061
Sad life.

349
00:18:09,181 --> 00:18:09,901
- [Trish] So sad.
- You know, 20 years alone

350
00:18:09,941 --> 00:18:11,821
in that tank.

351
00:18:11,941 --> 00:18:13,501
- [Trish] Hmm. I know.
- And then she gets injured.

352
00:18:13,581 --> 00:18:15,021
Can't do any of the...
the little show tricks.

353
00:18:15,141 --> 00:18:16,781
- [Trish] Yeah, yeah.
- So they breed her.

354
00:18:16,901 --> 00:18:18,701
- And then her baby dies.
- [Trish] Poseidon.

355
00:18:18,821 --> 00:18:20,421
- "Or dies." Yeah.
- [Trish] Yeah.

356
00:18:20,501 --> 00:18:22,861
[Josh] See, I think they stole the baby.

357
00:18:22,941 --> 00:18:25,701
And that's how Ceto got that
nasty scar across her face.

358
00:18:25,821 --> 00:18:27,861
That's crazy.
I think the exact same thing.

359
00:18:27,941 --> 00:18:29,901
Mm-hmm. Greedy arseholes
profiting her from pain.

360
00:18:29,941 --> 00:18:32,501
Ah, says he, displaying the brochure.

361
00:18:32,621 --> 00:18:33,821
[Josh] Fair point. Here, look.

362
00:18:35,541 --> 00:18:36,541
[Trish] Oh!

363
00:18:37,461 --> 00:18:40,101
Wow, way to stick it to the man.

364
00:18:40,181 --> 00:18:41,821
Oh, you want to stick it to the man, huh?

365
00:18:42,141 --> 00:18:43,941
- Sure.
- [Josh] Great.

366
00:18:44,061 --> 00:18:46,541
We'll just kick back.
Wait for nightfall to come.

367
00:18:46,621 --> 00:18:48,021
And then we go show them what's up.

368
00:18:48,221 --> 00:18:49,221
What do you think?

369
00:18:50,421 --> 00:18:51,581
- I love that idea.
- I don't.

370
00:18:55,941 --> 00:18:56,941
Great.

371
00:18:58,181 --> 00:19:00,781
[upbeat music playing]

372
00:19:01,261 --> 00:19:03,501
[indistinct chatter]

373
00:19:07,741 --> 00:19:10,301
[laughing]

374
00:19:10,381 --> 00:19:12,941
[upbeat music continues]

375
00:19:24,821 --> 00:19:26,781
[exclaiming]

376
00:19:26,861 --> 00:19:28,501
[upbeat music ends]

377
00:19:28,581 --> 00:19:30,461
- [Maddie laughing]
- [Trish laughing]

378
00:19:32,141 --> 00:19:33,781
Whoa, whoa, whoa.

379
00:19:34,301 --> 00:19:38,141
Okay, okay. So, maybe, maybe

380
00:19:38,261 --> 00:19:41,021
the booze and the pills
weren't the best idea.

381
00:19:41,141 --> 00:19:41,941
[Trish laughs]

382
00:19:42,101 --> 00:19:43,181
Give it back.

383
00:19:46,821 --> 00:19:47,821
Are we doing this?

384
00:19:50,101 --> 00:19:53,301
Hey, you are not
financially endorsing this.

385
00:19:54,261 --> 00:19:55,421
- I'm not.
- [Trish] You're not.

386
00:19:55,541 --> 00:19:56,901
You're just coming to say hi.

387
00:19:56,941 --> 00:19:58,501
- Just say hi.
- It's going to be fun.

388
00:19:58,621 --> 00:20:00,101
- Just say hi.
- It's going to be so much fun.

389
00:20:00,181 --> 00:20:01,701
- Okay, I'll say hi.
- [Trish giggling]

390
00:20:01,781 --> 00:20:04,501
[unsettling music playing]

391
00:20:07,661 --> 00:20:08,661
[Trish] Oh.

392
00:20:11,341 --> 00:20:13,701
- [Josh] Shh.
- [Trish laughs]

393
00:20:13,781 --> 00:20:15,101
[Josh] Go, go, go, go. [Chuckles]

394
00:20:16,421 --> 00:20:19,581
[unsettling music continues]

395
00:20:20,421 --> 00:20:23,381
- [Trish laughing]
- [Josh] No, this way.

396
00:20:23,461 --> 00:20:25,501
[Josh whispers] You have to be quiet.

397
00:20:27,381 --> 00:20:28,701
[Maddie] Wait up guys!

398
00:20:30,861 --> 00:20:32,861
[Trish giggling] Put me down.

399
00:20:33,941 --> 00:20:36,341
- [Josh] Woah, woah, woah.
- [Maddie] Oh, oh my God!

400
00:20:38,181 --> 00:20:39,181
[Maddie] Hold on.

401
00:20:39,861 --> 00:20:42,541
[unsettling music continues]

402
00:20:44,461 --> 00:20:45,461
[Trish] Let's go!

403
00:20:48,021 --> 00:20:50,341
[Trish] Okay. Okay, come on, come on.

404
00:20:54,101 --> 00:20:55,421
I don't know guys.

405
00:20:55,941 --> 00:20:57,781
What if seeing her in person
is worse than...

406
00:20:58,341 --> 00:21:00,221
She's not going to fit in your suitcase.

407
00:21:00,821 --> 00:21:02,501
At least you get
to have a moment with her.

408
00:21:03,181 --> 00:21:04,181
Go see the whale.

409
00:21:05,101 --> 00:21:07,541
Okay. Go. See the whale.

410
00:21:08,701 --> 00:21:09,701
[button clicks]

411
00:21:16,301 --> 00:21:20,581
[unsettling music continues]

412
00:21:25,541 --> 00:21:27,581
- [electricity zapping]
- [Ceto calling]

413
00:21:34,221 --> 00:21:36,581
[unsettling music fades]

414
00:21:39,701 --> 00:21:42,381
[rumbling]

415
00:21:50,941 --> 00:21:53,941
[hearing aid screeches]

416
00:21:58,541 --> 00:22:01,261
[dramatic music playing]

417
00:22:03,821 --> 00:22:05,061
[Ceto calls]

418
00:22:07,061 --> 00:22:10,461
- [dramatic music continues]
- [Ceto calling]

419
00:22:19,301 --> 00:22:22,461
[dramatic music continues]

420
00:22:23,781 --> 00:22:24,781
[chuckles]

421
00:22:25,341 --> 00:22:26,221
Hi.

422
00:22:26,301 --> 00:22:29,141
[Ceto calling]

423
00:22:35,701 --> 00:22:36,781
What have they done to you?

424
00:22:46,221 --> 00:22:48,901
[music becomes somber]

425
00:22:52,141 --> 00:22:53,541
I'm so sorry, Ceto.

426
00:22:55,941 --> 00:22:57,341
I'm sorry you're trapped in there.

427
00:22:59,581 --> 00:23:00,941
[water splashes]

428
00:23:02,341 --> 00:23:03,461
Trish!

429
00:23:05,941 --> 00:23:06,821
Josh!

430
00:23:06,941 --> 00:23:08,501
[Josh] Busy!

431
00:23:08,581 --> 00:23:09,941
He's fine, leave him alone.

432
00:23:11,541 --> 00:23:12,541
[gasps]

433
00:23:13,941 --> 00:23:14,941
[screams]

434
00:23:15,501 --> 00:23:17,541
[pants]

435
00:23:17,661 --> 00:23:19,061
[suspenseful music playing]

436
00:23:31,301 --> 00:23:32,781
Oh my God!

437
00:23:33,621 --> 00:23:35,301
- [Trish laughing]
- [Josh laughing]

438
00:23:35,421 --> 00:23:37,581
You guys, guys. We have to go.
We have to go now.

439
00:23:37,661 --> 00:23:39,621
- Hey!
- Maddie!

440
00:23:39,701 --> 00:23:41,821
I... I saw, there was...
there was a body in the tank.

441
00:23:42,781 --> 00:23:44,661
Hey! What are you doing here?

442
00:23:44,741 --> 00:23:46,181
- Oh! Go, go, go, go.
- Go!

443
00:23:47,141 --> 00:23:48,141
[Security] Hey!

444
00:23:48,861 --> 00:23:51,701
- [exclaims]
- [Trish] Go, go, go!

445
00:23:53,661 --> 00:23:56,301
- [Josh grunts] Let's go!
- Hurry, hurry. Go, go, go, go.

446
00:23:56,381 --> 00:23:57,941
- [Guard] Stop!
- [Josh] Go, go, go!

447
00:23:59,301 --> 00:24:00,901
- [Guarfd] Wait!
- [Maddie grunts]

448
00:24:02,101 --> 00:24:04,781
- [grunting]
- [Guard] You, stop! Wait.

449
00:24:04,901 --> 00:24:07,181
- [grunts]
- [suspenseful music fades]

450
00:24:15,861 --> 00:24:16,861
Come in.

451
00:24:18,261 --> 00:24:20,301
- [man] What?
- The cleaner.

452
00:24:21,181 --> 00:24:22,181
The cleaner.

453
00:24:22,941 --> 00:24:25,221
- In Ceto's tank.
- Again?!

454
00:24:25,781 --> 00:24:27,461
- Yeah.
- Get rid of that damn fish!

455
00:24:27,541 --> 00:24:29,861
- [waves crashing]
- [unsettling music playing]

456
00:24:36,181 --> 00:24:38,061
- [Trish laughing]
- [Josh laughing]

457
00:24:38,141 --> 00:24:40,221
- Shh.
- [seagulls mewing]

458
00:24:43,901 --> 00:24:44,901
Good morning.

459
00:24:45,821 --> 00:24:48,261
- Hi. Hi!
- Hi.

460
00:24:49,181 --> 00:24:50,301
Hi.

461
00:24:50,421 --> 00:24:51,621
We have...

462
00:24:52,701 --> 00:24:54,381
a surprise for you.

463
00:24:54,501 --> 00:24:56,701
Thanks. But, I've had
enough surprises for one trip.

464
00:24:56,781 --> 00:24:58,621
Trish, I'm good.

465
00:24:58,701 --> 00:25:00,381
No, no, no, no.
Please, trust me. You're...

466
00:25:00,941 --> 00:25:01,941
you're going to love it.

467
00:25:03,421 --> 00:25:04,501
I promise.

468
00:25:05,541 --> 00:25:07,941
- ["Follow My Shadow" playing]
- [jet ski engine revving]

469
00:25:11,701 --> 00:25:14,621
[Trish exclaims]

470
00:25:18,341 --> 00:25:19,661
[exclaims]

471
00:25:31,941 --> 00:25:33,821
[song fades]

472
00:25:36,861 --> 00:25:38,781
- [life jackets zipping]
- [Josh grunts]

473
00:25:38,861 --> 00:25:40,101
- [Josh] Thank you.
- [Maddie] Thanks.

474
00:25:40,221 --> 00:25:41,581
Trish. Trish?

475
00:25:41,661 --> 00:25:43,381
[mystical music playing]

476
00:25:48,781 --> 00:25:50,141
This is amazing.

477
00:25:52,461 --> 00:25:53,461
What's it called?

478
00:25:53,901 --> 00:25:55,701
[sighs] Well, I could tell you.

479
00:25:56,821 --> 00:25:57,941
But then I have to kill you.

480
00:25:59,821 --> 00:26:02,381
[Maddie] I don't understand.
How come nobody's here but us?

481
00:26:02,461 --> 00:26:04,181
[Josh] Apparently
a bunch of stuff happened,

482
00:26:04,501 --> 00:26:06,221
a couple years ago.

483
00:26:06,301 --> 00:26:07,781
And no one ever really came back since.

484
00:26:07,901 --> 00:26:09,741
The locals say it's cursed.

485
00:26:11,781 --> 00:26:13,701
But I say it's a great hangover cure.

486
00:26:15,621 --> 00:26:16,741
- I hope so.
- [scoffs]

487
00:26:19,301 --> 00:26:20,701
Is that thing glued to her hand?

488
00:26:22,181 --> 00:26:25,501
Yep. Along with 850,000 followers.

489
00:26:26,541 --> 00:26:28,061
Is it what she does for a living?

490
00:26:28,181 --> 00:26:29,541
[Trish] Well, till I finish my thesis

491
00:26:29,621 --> 00:26:31,341
on the use of immune modification

492
00:26:31,421 --> 00:26:32,941
through gene editing
to combat stem cell damage.

493
00:26:33,101 --> 00:26:34,101
Yeah.

494
00:26:34,541 --> 00:26:36,621
- Right. Well, okay.
- Yeah.

495
00:26:36,701 --> 00:26:38,621
[chuckles] Okay, well, I didn't
understand a lot of those words.

496
00:26:38,701 --> 00:26:41,581
What I do know is
I think you've had a little

497
00:26:41,701 --> 00:26:43,461
- too much screen time today.
- [Trish] Excuse me! Excuse me.

498
00:26:43,541 --> 00:26:44,741
Give me back my phone.

499
00:26:45,381 --> 00:26:46,381
[grunts]

500
00:26:47,421 --> 00:26:48,661
[Josh] Relax.

501
00:26:49,461 --> 00:26:51,421
It'll be safe. It'll be
right here in the jet ski.

502
00:26:51,781 --> 00:26:52,781
[sighs]

503
00:26:54,301 --> 00:26:55,581
You've bring your phone, right?

504
00:26:56,261 --> 00:26:58,141
- Yes, I have my phone.
- [whispers] Thank God.

505
00:27:01,661 --> 00:27:02,941
