1007
00:59:37,541 --> 00:59:40,381
- [phone line trilling]
- [dramatic music continues]

1008
00:59:41,781 --> 00:59:44,861
He left me a voicemail,
but it was too late.

1009
00:59:48,541 --> 00:59:50,781
He was never meant to bring a gun!

1010
00:59:52,501 --> 00:59:53,501
[gunshot fires]

1011
00:59:56,101 --> 00:59:58,701
[dramatic music intensifies]

1012
00:59:58,821 --> 00:59:59,821
[gunshot fires]

1013
01:00:00,661 --> 01:00:01,661
So I left.

1014
01:00:02,901 --> 01:00:03,901
I left you.

1015
01:00:07,421 --> 01:00:09,781
[cries]

1016
01:00:09,901 --> 01:00:11,901
[sobbing, sniffles]

1017
01:00:15,341 --> 01:00:19,221
You have to know
that every day when I wake up,

1018
01:00:19,341 --> 01:00:21,581
every night when I go to sleep, all I can...

1019
01:00:22,141 --> 01:00:25,461
all I can think about is how
I wish I could go back in time

1020
01:00:25,581 --> 01:00:28,221
and pick up that call.
Maddie, you have to believe me.

1021
01:00:28,341 --> 01:00:29,621
You have to believe me.

1022
01:00:33,901 --> 01:00:37,221
[somber music playing]

1023
01:00:40,941 --> 01:00:41,941
[distantly] Maddie.

1024
01:00:42,941 --> 01:00:44,301
I'm so sorry...

1025
